// Default cosmic-comp output config for the bootc/OCI image. Pinned to
// 1680x1050 on QEMU's virtio-vga-gl connector so the compositor doesn't
// boot at the EDID-default 640x480. cosmic-initial-setup caps its
// window at 900x650 (src/main.rs:80) -- 1680x1050 leaves comfortable
// margin around the full Create-Account form (avatar + 4 inputs +
// buttons). Smaller resolutions like 1280x800 hide the password
// fields below the visible card area.
//
// Format / matching semantics (from pop-os/cosmic-comp epoch-1.0.11,
// cosmic-comp-config/src/output/comp.rs):
//   - File lives at $XDG_STATE_HOME/cosmic-comp/outputs.ron (~/.local/state).
//   - HashMap is keyed by the *full set* of connected outputs as
//     [(connector, make, model)]. cosmic-comp computes that key from
//     EDID at startup and looks it up; a non-match means it falls back
//     to the connector's preferred mode (640x480 for QEMU's auto-EDID).
//     "Red Hat, Inc." / "QEMU Monitor" are exactly what QEMU 10.x
//     advertises -- verified against a running VM's persisted file.
//   - mode is ((width, height), Some(refresh_in_millihertz)). cosmic-comp
//     filters connector modes by exact pixel-size match, then picks the
//     mode whose refresh rate is closest to the configured value
//     (src/backend/kms/mod.rs around line 860). 60000 mHz snaps to the
//     CVT-RB ~59.81 Hz mode QEMU advertises for 1280x800.
//
// This file is copied per-user via tmpfiles.d (C-type) on first boot.
// Once the smithay PR #1923 fix propagates to cosmic-comp, dynamic
// resize will work and this preset becomes a soft default the user can
// override by changing display settings.
(
    config: {
        [
            (
                connector: "Virtual-1",
                make: "Red Hat, Inc.",
                model: "QEMU Monitor",
            ),
        ]: [
            (
                mode: ((1680, 1050), Some(60000)),
                vrr: r#false,
                scale: 1.0,
                transform: Normal,
                position: (0, 0),
                enabled: r#true,
                xwayland_primary: true,
            ),
        ],
    },
)
